                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 12.039,
                                "byte_start": 81045,
                                "byte_stop": 129215,
                                "text": "In the Lyng case No. 86-1013, the case comes to us on certiorari from the United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 12.039,
                                "stop": 18.555,
                                "byte_start": 129215,
                                "byte_stop": 155337,
                                "text": "It involves a dispute about the scope of the First Amendment right to the free exercise of religion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 18.555,
                                "stop": 30.511,
                                "byte_start": 155337,
                                "byte_stop": 203194,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals approved a permanent injunction forbidding the Federal Government from constructing a road through the Chimney Rock area of the Six Rivers National Forest in California."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 30.511,
                                "stop": 40.39,
                                "byte_start": 203194,
                                "byte_stop": 242691,
                                "text": "This area of the National Forest has traditionally been used for religious rituals by members of three American-Indian tribes that live nearby."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 40.39,
                                "stop": 52.605,
                                "byte_start": 242691,
                                "byte_stop": 291487,
                                "text": "Those religious practices which require privacy, silence, and an undisturbed natural setting can only be carried out at specific sites in the Chimney Rock area."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 52.605,
                                "stop": 63.32,
                                "byte_start": 291487,
                                "byte_stop": 334328,
                                "text": "The Court below found that the proposed road would so disturb the natural environment that it would virtually destroy the Indians\u0027 ability to practice their religion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 63.32,
                                "stop": 70.157,
                                "byte_start": 334328,
                                "byte_stop": 361705,
                                "text": "The Court also found that the government had failed to demonstrate a compelling interest in completing the project."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 70.157,
                                "stop": 87.371,
                                "byte_start": 361705,
                                "byte_stop": 430563,
                                "text": "Using a balancing test to weight the Indians\u0027 interest and that of the United States, the Court of Appeals concluded that the Indians\u0027 right to their free exercise of their religion would be unconstitutionally infringed by the government\u0027s proposed activities in the Chimney Rock area."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 87.371,
                                "stop": 92.394,
                                "byte_start": 430563,
                                "byte_stop": 450625,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed today, we reverse the judgment of the Court of Appeals."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 92.394,
                                "stop": 109.802,
                                "byte_start": 450625,
                                "byte_stop": 520320,
                                "text": "Two terms ago in the case of Bowen against Roy, we held that the Free Exercise Clause cannot be understood to require the government to conduct its own internal affairs in ways that comport with the religious belief of particular citizens."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 109.802,
                                "stop": 125.327,
                                "byte_start": 520320,
                                "byte_stop": 582387,
                                "text": "In that case as in this one, the government\u0027s management of its internal affairs threaten to interfere significantly with the ability of private people to pursue spiritual fulfillment according to their own religious beliefs."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 125.327,
                                "stop": 140.607,
                                "byte_start": 582387,
                                "byte_stop": 643514,
                                "text": "In neither case, however, did the government\u0027s proposed action threatened either to coerce religious adherence and the acting contrary to their belief or to penalize religious adherence for exercising their religious freedom."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 140.607,
                                "stop": 151.48,
                                "byte_start": 643514,
                                "byte_stop": 686981,
                                "text": "Our decision in Bowen against Roy, therefore, compels us to conclude that the free exercise challenge to the government\u0027s construction project must fail."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 151.48,
                                "stop": 163.816,
                                "byte_start": 686981,
                                "byte_stop": 736405,
                                "text": "We note, however, that the government\u0027s right to manage the public lands need not and should not discourage it from accommodating religious practices like those at issue in this case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 163.816,
                                "stop": 178.685,
                                "byte_start": 736405,
                                "byte_stop": 795860,
                                "text": "The American-Indian Religious Freedom Act establishes a national policy in favor of protecting and preserving the right of Indians to visit their traditional religious sites and to carry out their traditional rituals."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 178.685,
                                "stop": 192.117,
                                "byte_start": 795860,
                                "byte_stop": 849567,
                                "text": "Although this statute does not create enforceable legal rights, it does encourage the government to minimize the extent to which its management of the public lands interferes with Indian religious practices."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 192.117,
                                "stop": 205.37,
                                "byte_start": 849567,
                                "byte_stop": 902544,
                                "text": "In this case the government has planned various ways for minimizing the effects that its road will have on the Chimney Rock area and nothing in our decision should discourage such ameliorative measures."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 205.37,
                                "stop": 211.612,
                                "byte_start": 902544,
                                "byte_stop": 927517,
                                "text": "The case is remanded for deciding certain statutory issues, which we have not addressed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 211.612,
                                "stop": 217.398,
                                "byte_start": 927517,
                                "byte_stop": 950714,
                                "text": "Justice Brennan has filed a dissenting opinion in which Justices Marshall and Blackmun have joined."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 217.398,
                                "stop": 221.884,
                                "byte_start": 950714,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Kennedy took no part in the consideration or decision of the case."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
